Chairman Cubana Group Obinna Iyiegbu aka Obi Cubana has stated investing in humans is the undoubtedly the best investment there is. The Abuja-based socialite, who is also well-known for his philanthropic gestures, encouraged individuals never to relent in doing good deed to others. According to the entrepreneur, a person’s good deeds would always endear them to many who would be willing to fight their battles both known and unknown.   How I escaped robbery, kidnapping in Lagos traffic, by…     Burna Boy dazzles over 20,000 fans at iconic Madison Square…     I was created to enjoy life, says Regina Daniels   Though Obi Cubana acknowledged the existence of a few terrible persons but maintained the numbers of the good ones are way more. He wrote: “I keep saying that the best investment in life is in human beings!!” wrote the nightlife boss. “Some battles are fought and won on your behalf by people you’ve been good to, or people you may never have encountered but see u as being good to others!!! “Forget a few terrible humans, a lot of people are still very good humans!!! Keep being good to fellow humans!!!”